race.comment: Wide open race. SAVATOFF (3) is going much better than his form suggests. Won two on end then was not far away in tougher before a midfield finish last time. Goes well here and drawn for a soft run. Gets his chance to find winning form again. KING OF WESSEX (4) will be well fancied. Has been edging towards a win, the latest finishing runner-up here at the same trip when beaten just a head. Peaks now after four runs back and expected to go close. SEA TREASURES (10) was thereabouts over the trip here last time in tougher class. Tricky gate to overcome but well placed here on recent form here at the trip. CHARTIN (11) has been pushing forward and giving a sight, the latest when just missed over 2200m at Balaklava. Drawn to be prominent and will give a sight.
